korean:
  title: 응제
  author: 이암
  language: kor
  text: |-
    옥련이 친히 송악에 다다르니
    영지(불로초(不老草))는 돌정자 사이에 빼어났구나
    우리 왕의 거룩한 덕을 어찌 다 말하겠노
    먼저 그 천령이 이 산과 같기를 축하하네
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0240_010_0180&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: In Response to the Royal Commission
  author: Lee Am
  language: eng
  text: |-
    The jade palanquin descends upon Songnak's heights,
    Where immortal fungus blooms between stone pavilions.
    How could words capture our sovereign's sacred virtue?
    First, I celebrate that Heaven's blessings match this mountain's eternal span.
  footnotes:
    - 'Songnak (松嶺/송악): A sacred mountain, often associated with imperial journeys and blessings'
    - The jade palanquin and immortal fungus are traditional symbols of imperial majesty and longevity in East Asian court poetry
    - This appears to be a court poem commissioned to commemorate a royal visit, a common literary form in classical Korean kingdoms
